description: New Latin rosulatus, from rosa (“a rose”).

adjectives.description: rosulate (comparative more rosulate, superlative most rosulate)

entries.meaning: (botany, of leaves and bracts) Arranged in small rose-like clusters.
examples: It appears to claim a very close relationship to the preceding species, differing chiefly in the tiny leaves being rather more rosulate than caudiculate, and in not being adpressed, but rather the reverse; its petals, also, are narrower.
